article.headline: Iowa State 79, Kansas 57
article.story:
AMES, Iowa (AP) -- Erica Junod had 17 points and five assists in
her last home game, leading Iowa State to a 79-57 victory over
Kansas on Thursday night in the regular-season finale for both.

Lyndsey Medders added 13 points and Lisa Kriener scored 12 for
the Cyclones (14-13, 7-9 Big 12), who built a 47-31 halftime lead
and were never threatened.

Kansas (9-18, 2-14) shot only 33 percent and lost for the ninth
straight time. Tamara Ransburg led the Jayhawks with 19 points and
Crystal Kemp scored 10.

Iowa State, seeded ninth, will play eighth-seeded Nebraska in
the first round of the Big 12 tournament at noon next Tuesday in
Dallas. Kansas, the No. 12 seed, will play fifth-seeded Baylor at
2:30 p.m. Tuesday.

Junod, Iowa State's only senior, went 6-for-10 from the field
with three 3-pointers. Medders, a freshman, was 4-for-4 from
3-point range and grabbed six rebounds.

Medders and Megan Ronhovde each hit a 3-pointer to give Iowa
State a quick 6-0 lead and the Cyclones were ahead the rest of the
way.

Kansas didn't make its first basket until Larisha Graves scored
3 1/2 minutes into the game. Midway through the first half, Iowa
State led 24-7 and Kansas was 3-for-14 from the field.

Iowa State led by 24 late in the half. Baskets by Katie
Robinette and Anne O'Neil in the first minute of the second half
gave Iowa State a 51-31 lead and the Jayhawks never got closer than
17 after that.
